# isEqual(to:)

**Instance Method**

Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the contents of the receiving dictionary are equal to the contents of another given dictionary.

## Declaration

```swift
func isEqual(to otherDictionary: [AnyHashable : Any]) -> Bool
```

## Parameters

- **otherDictionary**: The dictionary with which to compare the receiving dictionary.

## Return Value

[doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Swift/true] if the contents of `otherDictionary` are equal to the contents of the receiving dictionary, otherwise [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Swift/false].

## Discussion

Two dictionaries have equal contents if they each hold the same number of entries and, for a given key, the corresponding value objects in each dictionary satisfy the [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ObjectiveC/NSObjectProtocol/isEqual(_:)] test.

## Related Documentation

- **isEqual(_:)**: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the receiver and a given object are equal.
